body:
@drcrallen @fjy as per the discussion I had with one of our users @premc . He wants to be able to run kill tasks automatically in production as it saves him a lot of operational headache. So, this PR changes in following ways to make it safer in production.

1) kill task schedule now has its own dataSource whitelist , kill task for a dataSource is sent if and only if the dataSource exists in the whitelist. (if whitelist is null then no kill tasks are sent)
2) added support for a property called `druid.coordinator.kill.durationToRetain` (default 1 Year), so kill task interval is set to [0, currentTime - durationToRetain].
